&lt;div id="outline-container-sec-3" class="outline-2"&gt;
&lt;h2 id="sec-3"&gt;Well…&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="outline-text-2" id="text-3"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
The idea is to create a blogging website hosted in &lt;i&gt;Github&lt;/i&gt;, using a
static site generator software &lt;i&gt;Nikola&lt;/i&gt;, with the help of &lt;i&gt;Python
virtual environment&lt;/i&gt; and then write blog posts using &lt;i&gt;emacs org mode&lt;/i&gt;.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id="outline-container-sec-3-0-1" class="outline-4"&gt;
&lt;h4 id="sec-3-0-1"&gt;Also&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;div class="outline-text-4" id="text-3-0-1"&gt;
&lt;ol class="org-ol"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;I'm using Linux.
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;I will be assuming the name of your blog as 'bottle'
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id="outline-container-sec-4" class="outline-2"&gt;
&lt;h2 id="sec-4"&gt;GitHub&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="outline-text-2" id="text-4"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Create a GitHub account. Create a repository with the following name:
'bottle.github.io'. &lt;a href="https://guides.github.com/activities/hello-world/"&gt;Instructions&lt;/a&gt;.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
Once you do this, then GitHub will host your website in the following
address(URL) : &lt;a href="https://bottle.github.io/"&gt;https://bottle.github.io/&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
Clone(copy) this newborn repository into your local machine a.k.a
personal computer by using the following command:
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;$ git clone https://bottle.github.io/ ~/projects/bottle
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
You will be adding blog posts in ~/projects/bottle directory and will
push them back to GitHub later.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
